<p>Sherry drank coffee to recover from her first stint at action. Hans glided behind her, silent as a memory. He reached down towards her. She blinked and looked up at him. &quot;Did you need something, Hans?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;You're aware. That's good. What did Glass's readings say?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Just one thread. 3 comments, one of them a bot.&quot; She tried to ignore as Hans sat beside her, too close.</p>
<p>&quot;You trust Glass?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Yeah, sure. He introduced us.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Through a pane,&quot; Hans said as he poured himself more coffee.</p>
<p>&quot;He said it was necessary.&quot;</p>
<p>Hans grunted and drank, then moved to leave the break room.</p>
<p>&quot;Wait, Hans.&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;Hm?&quot;</p>
<p>&quot;How do you make a NoPage profile?&quot;</p>
